title: Coaches' Corner: UMD Hockey's Scott Sandelin
text:
Coaches' Corner: UMD Hockey's Scott Sandelin 
By Zach Schneider October 14, 2015 Updated Oct 14, 2015 at 11:28 AM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) men's hockey team opened the 2015-16 season this past weekend with a 3-2 loss to Bemidji State, and that was a main part of the discussion in this week's "Coaches' Corner" with head coach Scott Sandelin. 
This conversation is part of the weekly show "Bulldog Country," which covers all things UMD and airs every Friday night at 6:30 p.m. on the My 9 Sports Network.
